  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">OSF will use funds to raise awareness among community members and civil society about basic human rights; to organize volunteers to monitor, document and respond to increasing human rights abuses and land seizures; to encourage the government to amend the current land use act; and to draw national and international attention to the plights of the Ogoni farmers and to promote international campaign against land grabbing and food insecurity that has been caused by massive oil pollution in Ogoni. This will be done in part by organizing a round table discussion on the land use act; raising awareness in the six kingdoms of Ogoni about land grabbing; to do a briefing paper and advocacy visit to call for the amendment of the land use act; and to document rights abuses.</narrative>
  </description>
